            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription, written in a different colour to the dedicatory epigram above (see MedCY.044.104), may have been added when this and the fresco of Saint George on horseback were completed. Consequently, Nikephoros the farrier is probably a different person from the veterinarian Nikephoros, mentioned in the dedicatory epigram (<bibl><ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>,<citedRange> 83</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#VisCult"/>,<citedRange> 189</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
            </div>
